name="source">MML <fr:link
type="external"
href="https://mizar.uwb.edu.pl/version/current/html/field_12.html#T25">field_12:25</fr:link></fr:meta><fr:meta
name="source">Lang <fr:link
type="local"
href="lang-2002-algebra.xml"
addr="lang-2002-algebra"
title="Algebra">Algebra</fr:link> Theorem V.2.8</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be a field, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be an algebraic extension, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i:\mathbb {F}\hookrightarrow \mathbb {L}]]></fr:tex> be an embedding of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> into an <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-001X.xml"
addr="nt-001X"
title="Algebraically Closed Field">algebraically closed</fr:link> field <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {L}]]></fr:tex>. Then:
<fr:ol><fr:li>There exists an extension of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i]]></fr:tex> to an embedding of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {L}]]></fr:tex>; and</fr:li>
<fr:li>If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> is algebraically closed and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {L}]]></fr:tex> is algebraic over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i(\mathbb {F})]]></fr:tex>, then any such extension of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i]]></fr:tex> is an isomorphism of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> onto <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {L}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol></fr:p>
 
   
